## 👮 Who Can Do What?

Authentication is "Who are you?". **Authorization** is "What are you allowed to do?". We use **RBAC** (Role-Based Access Control) to manage permissions.

---

## 1️⃣ Defining Roles

Common roles: `USER`, `INSTRUCTOR`, `ADMIN`.

```javascript
const roles = {
  USER: ['read:course'],
  ADMIN: ['read:course', 'delete:course', 'manage:users']
};
```

---

## 2️⃣ Guarding the Routes

We use middleware to check if a user has the right "Badge" (Role) before they enter a route.

```javascript
const isAdmin = (req, res, next) => {
  if (req.user.role !== 'ADMIN') return res.status(403).send("Access Denied");
  next();
};

app.delete('/course/:id', isAdmin, deleteCourse);
```

---

## 3️⃣ Permission Matrices

Instead of hard-coding roles everywhere, professional systems use an **Ability Matrix**. This makes it easy to add new roles or change what an `INSTRUCTOR` can do without editing 50 different files.

---

## 💡 Professional Tip
Always check authorization on the BACKEND. Just because a button is hidden in CSS doesn't mean a smart user can't find your API endpoint.
